<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<div type="elementDocumentation" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="objectIdentifierType">
    
    <head type="sematicunit">
        <abbr>1.1.1</abbr>
        <!-- PREMIS Semantic unit 1.1.1 -->
        <gi>objectIdentifierType</gi>
    </head>
    
    <div type="semanticcomponents">
        <!-- PREMIS Semantic components -->
        <p>None</p>
    </div>
    
    <div type="definition">
        <!-- PREMIS Definition -->
        <p>A designation of the domain within which the object identifier is
            unique.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div type="rationale">
        <!-- PREMIS Rationale -->
        <p>Identifier values cannot be assumed to be unique across domains; the
            combination of <bold>objectIdentifierType</bold> and
            <bold>objectIdentifierValue</bold> should ensure uniqueness.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div type="usagenotes">
        <!-- PREMIS Usage notes -->
        <p>The type of the identifier may be implicit within the repository as long
            as it can be explicitly communicated when the digital object is
            disseminated outside of it.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div type="datatype">
        <p>Value should be taken from a controlled vocabulary. A controlled
            vocabulary is available at <ref
                target="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/identifiers.html"
                >http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/identifiers.html</ref>.</p>
    </div>
    
